This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests it belongs to the Computer Science category. Within CS, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper deals with sentiment analysis and text classification. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper proposes a neural model for multi-task learning. The third most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with automated predictions and interpretability. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) since the paper deals with feature predictors and multi-dimensional masks. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) since the paper deals with the applicability of automated predictions in certain domains.
